The paper deals with video compressive sensing using deep learning frameworks, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. The authors also discuss the performance gains using deeper architectures, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves extensive simulations and analysis, which is related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
